%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20steps%20leaders%20must%20take%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20AI%20and%20not%20get%20left%20behind%2C%20according%20to%20an%20MBA%20professor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leigh%20Thompson.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F606e2af770954f0019195ca0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeigh%20Thompson.%3Cp%3ELeigh%20Thompson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeigh%20Thompson%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20Kellogg%20School%20of%20Management%20at%20Northwestern%20University.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20writes%20that%20we%20should%20not%20fight%20our%20urges%20to%20treat%20AI%20like%20a%20person.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThompson%20also%20says%20not%20to%C2%A0%26quot%3Btechno-stress%26quot%3B%20and%20to%20focus%20on%20adapting%20instead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20was%20a%20100-foot%20wave%20that%20forced%20managers%20to%20define%20and%20become%20their%20best%20%26quot%3Bvirtual%20self%26quot%3B%20for%20negotiations%20and%20other%20professional%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20generative%20AI%20is%20a%20mega-tsunami%20that%20will%20redefine%20leadership%20and%20work%20across%20sectors.%20It%20is%20simply%20a%20smarter%2C%20faster%2C%20tireless%20team%20member%20in%20many%20contexts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20think%20about%20how%20the%20growing%20presence%20of%20AI%20at%20work%20will%20influence%20your%20leadership%20behavior%20and%20communication%20style%2C%20to%20continue%20performing%20at%20your%20best%20%E2%80%94%20for%20yourself%20and%20your%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20social-organizational%20psychologist%20and%20professor%20at%20a%20top%20business%20school.%20Among%20other%20areas%2C%20I%20study%20how%20people's%20behavior%20changes%20when%20they%20engage%20in%20virtual%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20in-vivo%2C%20communication.%20I've%20found%20that%20by%20taking%20some%20specific%2C%20proactive%20steps%2C%20people%20can%20dramatically%20improve%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.igi-global.com%2Fchapter%2Fvirtual-intelligence-in-the-post-pandemic-era%2F309457%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evirtual%20communication%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20implications%20for%20how%20we%20can%20optimize%20our%20interactions%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20article%20I%20offer%20four%20big-picture%20tips%20for%20working%20with%20generative%20AI%2C%20to%20not%20just%20techno-survive%20but%20techno-thrive%20in%20this%20revolutionary%20phase%20of%20the%20Digital%20Age%2C%20using%20insights%20and%20research%20from%20psychology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Go%20with%20a%20growth%20mindset%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20ChatGPT's%20public%20launch%2C%20most%20managers%20had%20minimal%20experience%20using%20generative%20AI.%20That%20changed%20quickly%20as%20some%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fibm-managers-who-use-ai-will-replace-those-who-dont-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20IBM%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20suggested%20that%20managers%20start%20using%20AI%20or%20risk%20losing%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20is%20that%20generative%20AI%20has%20moved%20everyone%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20learning%20curve%2C%20forcing%20questions%20like%20%26quot%3BDo%20I%20have%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20this%20technology%20work%20for%20me%20and%20my%20company%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20better%20question%20for%20leaders%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20I%20believe%20I%20can%20learn%20to%20leverage%20generative%20AI%20in%20a%20productive%20way%3F%26quot%3B%20That's%20because%20the%20latter%20represents%20a%20growth%20mindset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarol%20Dweck's%20much-cited%20research%20on%20fixed-versus-growth%20mindsets%20revealed%20that%20some%20people%20believe%20that%20ability%20is%20innate%2C%20genetic%2C%20or%20otherwise%20immutable.%20Fixed-mindset%20beliefs%20like%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20spatial%20thinker%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI%20struggle%20with%20technology%26quot%3B%20can%20lead%20to%20withdrawal%2C%20fear%2C%20anxiety%2C%20and%20avoidance%20of%20new%20things%20or%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20seeing%20this%20at%20an%20organizational%20level%20with%20AI%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.personneltoday.com%2Fhr%2Fai-skills-gap%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20some%20leaders%20put%20the%20brakes%20on%20using%20generative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20based%20in%20part%20on%20perception%20of%20an%20AI-related%20skills%20gap%20among%20employees%20and%20the%20challenge%20of%20filling%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20head-in-the-sand%20approach%20is%20best-replaced%20with%20one%20embodying%20a%20growth%20mindset%3A%20that%20learning%20and%20performance%20are%20driven%20largely%20by%20motivation%2C%20grit%2C%20and%20practice%2C%20%2C%20including%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20new%20technologies.%20Look%20for%20research-backed%2C%20practical%20steps%20to%20embrace%20a%20growth%20mindset%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mindtheproduct.com%2Fwhy-im-not-afraid-of-ai-making-product-redundant%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuch%20as%20asking%20these%20two%20simple%20questions%3A%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BWhat%20can%20I%20do%20to%20help%20myself%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BIs%20there%20a%20way%20to%20do%20this%20even%20better%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Treat%20AI%20like%20a%20person%20%E2%80%94%20not%20a%20thing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGenerative%20AI's%20conversational%20style%20entices%20users%20to%20treat%20the%20technology%20as%20human.%20It%20may%20be%20tempting%20to%20fight%20that.%20Don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%3F%20Anthropomorphizing%20%E2%80%94%20or%20treating%20non-human%20entities%20as%20humans%20with%20personalities%20and%20emotions%20is%20natural.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20may%20feel%20silly%20interacting%20with%20generative%20AI%20like%20a%20human%2C%20using%20personal%20names%20and%20such%20(even%20though%20we%20already%20do%20with%20Alexa%2C%20Siri%2C%20and%20other%20personal%20devices).%20But%20research%20shows%20we%20experience%20better%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2018-12822-001%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20motivation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20learning%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fieeexplore.ieee.org%2Fabstract%2Fdocument%2F8897091%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20performance%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20anthropomorphizing%20things%20in%20our%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F0018720816687205%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoing%20so%20boosts%20oxytocin%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20brains%2C%20elevating%20trust%2C%20compliance%2C%20and%20team%20decision-making.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.aom.org%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.5465%2Famr.2016.0496%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20shows%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20moreover%2C%20that%20attributing%20human%20qualities%20to%20one's%20own%20organization%20(%26quot%3BOur%20company%20is%20caring%20and%20generous%26quot%3B)%20primes%20interpersonal%20emotions%20like%20empathy%20and%20accountability%2C%20with%20positive%20effects%20on%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20doing%20the%20same%20with%20AI%20should%20have%20similar%20positive%20effects.%20That%20gives%20you%20the%20greenlight%20to%20talk%20to%20AI%20as%20you%20would%20another%20human%2C%20including%20keeping%20the%20tip%20below%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Avoid%20power%20trips%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20design%2C%20generative%20AI%20puts%20us%20in%20a%20position%20of%20power%3A%20we%20provide%20a%20clear%2C%20short%20prompt%2C%20and%20it%20has%20to%20react%20(promptly).%20But%20this%20commanding%20communication%20style%20is%20less%20common%20with%20human%20interactions%2C%20and%20certainly%20less%20advisable.%20So%20we%20need%20to%20understand%20how%20being%20in%20a%20position%20of%20power%20with%20AI%20affects%20our%20psychology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20at%20that%20I%20did%20a%20recent%20experiment%20with%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%2C%20I%20treated%20the%20AI%20like%20a%20human%20assistant%20in%20my%20prompts%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHi%2C%20I'd%20love%20your%20help%20identifying%20scientific%20and%20business%20publications%20on%20virtual%20communication.%26quot%3B%20The%20next%20day%20I%20provided%20more%20terse%2C%20demanding%20prompts%3A%20%26quot%3BGive%20me%20no%20fewer%20than%2010%20publications%20on%20virtual%20communication%2C%20along%20with%20annotated%20bibliographies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20responses%20to%20the%20two%20types%20of%20prompts%20were%20similar%20in%20tone%20and%20content.%20But%20as%20I%20continued%20using%20a%20courteous%20or%20curt%20tone%2C%20ChatGPT's%20responses%20matched%20my%20communication%20style.%20The%20platform%20even%20began%20to%20hallucinate%20(present%20non-factual%20information%20as%20fact)%20more%20in%20response%20to%20my%20demanding%20prompts%2C%20and%20I%20began%20to%20feel%20frustrated%20with%20the%20process.%20That's%20consistent%20with%20social-psychology%20research%20showing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F14792779943000080%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20reciprocity%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20that%20people%20react%20to%20a%20given%20type%20of%20behavior%20in%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20go%20even%20further%2C%20my%20interaction%20with%20ChatGPT%20illuminated%20the%20danger%20of%20embracing%20a%20narrow%20role%20of%20any%20kind%2C%20as%20aligned%20with%20the%20creepy%20takeaway%20of%20Phil%20Zimbardo's%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Ftopics%2Fforensics-law-public-safety%2Fprison%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20infamous%20Stanford%20prison%20experiments%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20where%20university%20students%20assigned%20to%20be%20guards%20quickly%20became%20abusive%20over%20other%20students%20assigned%20to%20be%20prisoners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conclusion%20here%20is%20that%20to%20get%20the%20best%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20don't%20play%20into%20a%20dictator-servant%20relationship.%20Aim%20to%20build%20a%20collaborative%20relationship%20with%20the%20technology%20based%20on%20courtesy%20and%20respect%20%E2%80%94%20just%20as%20you%20would%2C%20hopefully%2C%20with%20a%20human%20colleague.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Don't%20techno-stress%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGenerative%20AI's%20recent%20rise%20wounded%20my%20pride.%20I've%20always%20been%20proud%20of%20my%20ability%20to%20write%20quickly%2C%20with%20high%20quality.%20But%20ChatGPT%20forced%20me%20to%20recognize%20one%20of%20my%20core%20competencies%20has%20been%20eclipsed%20%E2%80%94%20big%20time.%20AI%20can%20write%20everything%20from%20mission%20statements%20to%20book%20proposals%20in%20a%20tiny%20fraction%20of%20the%20time%20I%20would%20have%20taken%2C%20with%20reasonable%20accuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20me%2C%20many%20are%20experiencing%20similar%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faisel.aisnet.org%2Fpacis2023%2F126%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechno-stress%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20published%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20refers%20to%20the%20anxiety%20we%20feel%20when%20faced%20with%20learning%20new%20technologies.%20And%20it's%20not%20just%20writers%20or%20programmers%20who%20are%20feeling%20the%20bite%20of%20generative%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FAI.as%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI.as%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20new%20technology%20seeps%20into%20so%20many%20areas%20formerly%20dominated%20by%20humans.%20But%20facing%20a%20shift%20in%20identity%20needn't%20be%20alarming%20or%20depressing.%20Indeed%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Ftopics%2Fforensics-law-public-safety%2Fprison%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20shows%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20the%20attitude%20we%20maintain%20toward%20identity%20change%20is%20key%20to%20our%20future%20happiness%3A%20perceiving%20an%20identity%20shift%20as%20progressive%20promotes%20greater%20self-worth%20and%20positive%20emotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20of%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Btechno-thriving%26quot%3B%20(my%20own%20term)%2C%20or%20not%20merely%20adapting%20to%20new%20technologies%20but%20embracing%20them%20and%20making%20oneself%20open%20to%20learning%20and%20evolving.%20So%20how%20can%20you%20techno-thrive%3F%20By%20reassessing%20your%20strengths%20and%20weakness%20in%20service%20of%20aligning%20your%20actual%20and%20ideal%20selves.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20go%20from%20%26quot%3BI'm%20someone%20who%20struggles%20with%20technology%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3BI'm%20willing%20to%20learn%20new%20technologies%20and%20may%20be%20surprised%20by%20what%20I%20can%20do%20with%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20none%20of%20this%20is%20easy.%20As%20humans%2C%20we%20are%20naturally%20averse%20to%20change%2C%20and%20generative%20AI%20represents%20a%20tremendous%20shift%20in%20the%20way%20we%20work%2C%20create%2C%20and%20collaborate.%20But%20it's%20here%20to%20stay%2C%20so%20aim%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ELeigh%20Thompson%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20Kellogg%20School%20of%20Management%20at%20Northwestern%20University%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BNegotiating%20the%20Sweet%20Spot%3A%20The%20Art%20of%20Leaving%20Nothing%20on%20the%20Table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-ai-in-workplace-mba-professor-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691139601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cab28595fe1f0019df4e03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-ai-in-workplace-mba-professor-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Leigh%20Thompson%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Kellogg%20School%20of%20Management%2C%20says%20humans%20are%20naturally%20averse%20to%20change%20but%20AI%20is%20here%20to%20stay.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Leigh%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-use-ai-in-workplace-mba-professor-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Warren%20Buffett's%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20closes%20in%20on%20record%20high%20as%20its%20Apple%20stake%20and%20brighter%20outlook%20cheer%20investors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224518%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22warren%20buffett%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f199380f0f419158a795ff3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222259%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWarren%20Buffett.%3Cp%3EAP%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBerkshire%20Hathaway%20stock%20closed%20at%20a%2016-month%20high%2C%20and%20within%20touching%20distance%20of%20a%20new%20record.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWarren%20Buffett's%20company%20boasts%20a%20%24175%20billion%20stake%20in%20Apple%2C%20and%20benefits%20from%20a%20better%20economy.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBuffett%20has%20o