ul-gandhi-conviction-stay-criminal-defamation-case-modi-thieves-remark-234384%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20saying%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20sentence%20for%20an%20offence%20punishable%20under%20Section%20499%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20is%20maximum%20of%20two%20years%20of%20sentence%20or%20fine%20or%20both.%20The%20learned%20trial%20judge%2C%20in%20the%20order%20passed%20by%20him%2C%20has%20awarded%20the%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20two%20years.%20Except%20the%20admonition%20to%20the%20petitioner%20by%20this%20Court%20in%20a%20contempt%20proceeding%2C%20no%20other%20reason%20has%20been%20granted%20by%20the%20learned%20trial%20judge%20while%20imposing%20the%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20two%20years.%20It%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20it%20is%20only%20on%20account%20of%20the%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20two%20years%20imposed%20by%20the%20learned%20trial%20judge%20that%20the%20provisions%20of%20Section%208(3)%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20Peoples%20Act%20came%20into%20play.%20Had%20the%20sentence%20been%20a%20day%20lesser%2C%20then%20the%20provisions%20would%20not%20have%20attracted.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EParticularly%20when%20the%20offence%20was%20non-compoundable%2C%20bailable%20and%20cognizable%2C%20the%20least%20which%20was%20expected%20from%20the%20learned%20trial%20judge%20was%20to%20give%20reasons%20for%20imposing%20the%20maximum%20punishment.%20Though%20the%20learned%20appellate%20court%20and%20the%20High%20Court%20have%20spent%20voluminous%20pages%20in%20rejecting%20the%20applications%2C%20these%20aspects%20are%20not%20seen%20considered.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20however%2C%20also%20said%20that%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20in%20Kolar%20before%20the%202019%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20for%20which%20the%20case%20was%20filed%20%E2%80%93%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20in%20good%20taste%E2%80%9D.%20Gandhi%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20a%20question.%20Why%20do%20all%20these%20thieves%20have%C2%A0Modi%C2%A0in%20their%20names%20whether%20it%20is%20Nirav%C2%A0Modi%2C%20Lalit%C2%A0Modi%C2%A0or%20Narendra%C2%A0Modi%3F%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20many%20more%20such%20Modis%20will%20come%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20leader%20Purnesh%20Modi%20had%20filed%20a%20defamation%20case%20against%20Gandhi%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20had%20defamed%20the%20%E2%80%98Modi%20community%E2%80%99.%20Gandhi%20has%20maintained%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwill-not-apologise-for-remark-on-modi-surname-as-not-guilty-of-defamation-rahul-gandhi-to-sc%5C%22%3Ethat%20he%20is%20not%20guilty%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20so%20will%20not%20apologise%2C%20while%20also%20arguing%20that%20there%20is%20no%20one%20community%20of%20all%20people%20who%20share%20the%20Modi%20surname.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691137494000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21120741%2FUntitled-design-2-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-rahul-gandhis-conviction-in-defamation-case-questions-lower-court-on-sentence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22His%20disqualification%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20now%20stands%20in%20abeyance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-rahul-gandhis-conviction-in-defamation-case-questions-lower-court-on-sentence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Regressive%20Amendments%20to%20RTI%20Act%E2%80%99%3A%20NCPRI%20Flags%20Concerns%20Over%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%20(%3Cspan%3ENCPRI%3C%2Fspan%3E)%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%203%2C%20raised%20concerns%20over%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20was%20tabled%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20address%20key%20concerns%20pointed%20out%20by%20the%20rights%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20%3Cspan%3ENCPRI%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20that%20it%20had%20sent%20a%20detailed%20analysis%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill%2C%20which%20was%20put%20out%20for%20public%20consultation%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20(MEITY)%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20submission%20had%20highlighted%20key%20issues%20including%20the%20regressive%20amendments%20being%20made%20to%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20independence%20and%20autonomy%20of%20the%20oversight%20body%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Bill%20continues%20to%20suffer%20from%20the%20problems%20pointed%20out%20by%20NCPRI%20in%20the%20previous%20draft%2C%20read%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdata-protection-bill-opposition-parliamentary-committee%5C%22%3EOpposition%20Demands%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Be%20Sent%20to%20Parliamentary%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20statement%20is%20reproduced%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EStatement%20on%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20on%20August%203%2C%202023%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%20(NCPRI)%20is%20disappointed%20to%20note%20that%C2%A0%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%20(DPDP%20Bill)%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%C2%A0%20(3%2F8%2F2023)%20continues%20to%20suffer%20from%20the%20problems%20pointed%20out%20by%20NCPRI%20in%20the%20previous%20draft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NCPRI%20had%20sent%20a%20detailed%20analysis%2C%20which%20was%20also%20endorsed%20by%20groups%2Fcampaigns%C2%A0%20working%20on%20privacy%2C%20on%20the%20bill%20put%20out%20for%20public%20consultation%20by%20MEITY%20in%20November%202022.%C2%A0%20The%20submission%20had%20highlighted%20key%20issues%20including%20the%20regressive%20amendments%20being%20made%C2%A0%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20independence%20and%20autonomy%20of%20the%20oversight%20body-%20the%20Data%C2%A0%20Protection%20Board.%20We%20are%20disappointed%20to%20note%20that%20on%20both%20counts%2C%20the%20government%20has%20failed%C2%A0%20to%20address%20the%20concerns.%20The%20submission%20had%20also%20highlighted%20the%20need%20to%20adopt%20an%20extensive%C2%A0%20and%20rigorous%20pre-legislative%20consultation%20process%20for%20the%20proposed%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%20including%C2%A0%20ensuring%20dissemination%20of%20the%20draft%20bill%20through%20various%20modes%20and%20in%20multiple%20languages.%20The%C2%A0%20consultative%20process%20continued%20to%20be%20extremely%20narrow%20and%20seems%20to%20have%20largely%20focussed%C2%A0%20on%20the%20concerns%20of%20industry.%20The%20NCPRI%20was%20not%20invited%20for%20any%20consultation%20following%20the%C2%A0%20submission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20key%20concerns%20with%20the%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%202023%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%20are%3A%20%3Cb%3EAmendments%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%20(Section%2044(3))%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20proposed%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005%20through%20the%20DPDP%20Bill%20will%20severely%20restrict%C2%A0%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20adversely%20impact%20the%20ability%20of%20people%20to%20access%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%208(1)(j)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005%20states%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9C8.%20(1)%20Notwithstanding%20anything%20contained%20in%20this%20Act%2C%20there%20shall%20be%20no%20obligation%20to%C2%A0%20give%20any%20citizen%2C-%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3Exxx%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(j)%20information%20which%20relates%20to%20personal%20information%20the%20disclosure%20of%20which%20has%20no%C2%A0%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20activity%20or%20interest%2C%20or%20which%20would%20cause%20unwarranted%C2%A0%20invasion%20of%20the%20privacy%20of%20the%20individual%20unless%20the%20Central%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20or%C2%A0%20the%20State%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20or%20the%20appellate%20authority%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20is%C2%A0%20satisfied%20that%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%20justifies%20the%20disclosure%20of%20such%20information%3A%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exemption%20is%20not%20absolute%20and%20information%20has%20to%20be%20disclosed%20if%20it%20is%20such%20that%20cannot%20be%C2%A0%20denied%20to%20the%20Parliament%20or%20a%20State%20Legislature%20(proviso%20to%208(1))%2C%20if%20public%20interest%20in%20disclosure%20outweighs%20the%20harm%20to%20the%20protected%20interests%20(section%208(2))%20or%20if%20the%20information%20relates%20to%C2%A0%20any%20event%20or%20matter%20which%20has%20taken%20place%20twenty%20years%20ago%20(section%208(3)).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20DPDP%20Bill%20proposes%20the%20following%20amendments%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act-%20%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9C44(3)%20In%20section%208%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20in%20sub-section%20(1)%2C%20for%20clause%C2%A0%20(j)%2C%20the%20following%20clause%20shall%20be%20substituted%2C%20namely%3A%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9C(j)%20information%20which%20relates%20to%20personal%20information%3B%E2%80%9D.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20amendment%20to%20section%208(1)(j)%20of%20RTI%20Act%20therefore%20seeks%20to%20exempt%20%3Cb%3Eall%20personal%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3Einformation%3C%2Fb%3E.%20It%20does%20away%20with%20the%20exceptions%20carved%20out%20within%20the%20section%20based%20on%20which%20%C2%A0personal%20information%20could%20have%20been%20disclosed.%20Currently%2C%20in%20order%20to%20deny%20personal%20%C2%A0information%2C%20atleast%20one%20of%20the%20following%20grounds%20has%20to%20be%20proven-%20information%20sought%20has%20%C2%A0%3Cb%3Eno%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20activity%3B%20%3C%2Fb%3Eor%20information%20sought%20has%20%3Cb%3Eno%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3Einterest%3B%20%3C%2Fb%3Eor%20information%20sought%20would%20cause%20%3Cb%3Eunwarranted%20invasion%20of%20privacy%20%3C%2Fb%3Eand%20%C2%A0PIO%2Fappellate%20authority%20is%20satisfied%20that%20there%20is%20no%20larger%20public%20interest%20that%20justifies%20%C2%A0disclosure.%20The%20proposed%20blanket%20exemption%20is%20especially%20problematic%20since%20it%20does%20not%20limit%20%C2%A0the%20exemption%20from%20disclosure%20to%20only%20sensitive%20personal%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20proposal%20to%20amend%20the%20RTI%20Act%20through%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20drafted%20based%20on%20an%20incorrect%20understanding%20of%20the%20RTI%20law.%20The%20draft%20Bill%20errs%20in%C2%A0%20interpreting%20the%20proviso%20to%20section%208(1)%2C%20which%20states%20that%20%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9Cinformation%20which%20cannot%20be%20denied%C2%A0%20to%20the%20Parliament%20or%20a%20State%20Legislature%20shall%20not%20be%20denied%20to%20any%20person.%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3Eas%20being%20only%C2%A0%20applicable%20to%20section%208(1)(j)%20and%20not%20to%20the%20whole%20of%20section%208(1).%20A%20perusal%20of%20the%20original%C2%A0%20gazette%20notification%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20shows%20that%20by%20virtue%20of%20its%20placement%20and%20indentation%2C%20it%20is%C2%A0%20applicable%20to%20all%20of%20section%208(1)%20and%20not%20merely%20section%208(1)(j).%20There%20are%20several%20judicial%C2%A0%20pronouncements%20to%20this%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20well%20established%20that%20access%20to%20granular%20information%2C%20including%20personal%20information%2C%20is%20%C2%A0critical%20to%20empower%20people%20to%20undertake%20collective%20monitoring%20and%20ensure%20they%20are%20able%20to%20%C2%A0access%20their%20rights%20and%20entitlements.%20This%20principle%20is%20well%20recognised%20and%20has%20been%20adopted%20in%20%C2%A0various%20welfare%20programs%20and%20schemes.%20The%20proposed%20Bill%20will%20potentially%20place%20impediments%20%C2%A0and%20restrictions%20on%20such%20public%20disclosures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20proposed%20to%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%20through%20the%20Data%20Protection%C2%A0%20Bill%2C%20will%20fundamentally%20weaken%20the%20RTI%20Act%20for%20the%20reasons%20highlighted%20above.%20We%20believe%20that%C2%A0%20the%20legal%20framework%20for%20privacy%20and%20data%20protection%20should%20complement%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20in%20no%C2%A0%20way%20undermine%20or%20dilute%20the%20existing%20statutory%20framework%20that%20empowers%20citizens%20to%20hold%C2%A0%20power%20structures%20to%20account.%20The%20provisions%20of%20the%20Draft%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20need%20to%20be%C2%A0%20suitably%20amended%20and%20harmonized%20with%20the%20provisions%20and%20objectives%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act.%20This%C2%A0%20would%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Justice%20A.P.%20Shah%20Report%20on%20Privacy%20(2012)%C2%A0%20that%2C%20%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Privacy%20Act%20should%20clarify%20that%20publication%20of%20personal%20data%20%E2%80%A6%20in%20public%20interest%2C%20use%C2%A0%20of%20personal%20information%20for%20household%20purposes%2C%20and%20disclosure%20of%20information%20as%20required%20by%C2%A0%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20should%20not%20constitute%20an%20infringement%20of%20Privacy.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fi%3ENeither%20the%C2%A0%20recognition%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Privacy%2C%20nor%20the%20enactment%20of%20a%20data%20protection%20law%2C%20requires%20any%C2%A0%20amendment%20to%20the%20existing%20RTI%20law.%20Therefore%2C%20there%20should%20be%20no%20amendments%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExcessive%20powers%20vested%20in%20Central%20government%20%26amp%3B%20lack%20of%20independence%20of%20the%20Data%C2%A0%20Protection%20Board%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20the%20government%20is%20the%20biggest%20data%20repository%2C%20the%20law%20should%20not%20give%20wide%C2%A0%20discretionary%20powers%20to%20the%20executive.%20The%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20however%2C%20empowers%20the%C2%A0%20government%20to%20draft%20rules%20and%20notifications%20on%20a%20vast%20range%20of%20issues%20(S.%2040).%20The%20Union%C2%A0%20government%20can%20exempt%20any%20government%20or%20even%20private%20sector%20entity%20from%20the%20application%20of%C2%A0%20provisions%20of%20the%20law%20by%20merely%20issuing%20a%20notification%2C%20potentially%20resulting%20in%20immense%C2%A0%20violations%20of%20citizens%E2%80%99%20privacy%20(S.%2017(2)%20and%2017(3)).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20concerning%20to%20note%20the%20lack%20of%20autonomy%20of%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%2C%20the%20principal%C2%A0%20authority%20under%20the%20draft%20Bill%20to%20enforce%20compliance%20with%20the%20provisions%20of%20legislation.%20Section%C2%A0%2019%20of%20the%20bill%20vests%20in%20the%20Central%20Government%20wide%20powers%2C%20including%20appointing%20the%C2%A0%20Chairperson%20and%20members%20and%20deciding%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20Board.%20This%20lack%20of%20independence%C2%A0%20of%20the%20oversight%20mechanism%20is%20extremely%20worrying%20and%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20such%20a%20board%C2%A0%20function%20without%20the%20interference%20of%20the%20Central%20Government%20to%20enable%20the%20protection%20of%C2%A0%20rights%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20creation%20of%20a%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20not%20adequately%20independent%20of%20the%20government%2C%20with%C2%A0%20powers%20to%20impose%20fines%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%20250%20crore%20(the%20central%20government%20can%20raise%20the%20maximum%C2%A0%20penalty%20imposable%20under%20the%20law%20to%20Rs.%20500%20crore%20by%20amending%20the%20schedule)%2C%20raises%C2%A0%20apprehensions%20of%20potential%20misuse%20by%20the%20executive.%20(S.%2028%2C%20S.%2033%20%26amp%3B%20S.%2042)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20that%20the%20Board%20will%20be%20%E2%80%98digital%20by%20design%E2%80%99%2C%20including%20in%20the%20receipt%20of%20complaints%2C%C2%A0%20pronouncement%20of%20decision%20and%20other%20functions%2C%20will%20make%20it%20exclusionary%20and%20outside%20the%C2%A0%20reach%20of%20millions%20of%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEndorsed%20by%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnjali%20Bhardwaj%2C%20Nikhil%20Dey%2C%20Venkatesh%20Nayak%2C%20Rakesh%20Reddy%20Dubbudu%2C%20Pradip%20Pradhan%2C%20Pankti%C2%A0%20Jog%2C%20Dr.%20Shaikh%2C%20Shailesh%20Gandhi%2C%20Amrita%20Johri%2C%20Bhaskar%20Prabhu%2C%20Chakradhar%20Buddha%2C%20Ajay%C2%A0%20Jangid%2C%20Karuna%20M.%2C%20Praveer%20Peter%20(On%20behalf%20of%20the%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%C2%A0%20Information)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691137488000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fregressive-amendments-to-rti-act-ncpri-flags-concerns-over-digital-personal-data-protection-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NCPRI%20said%20that%20it'd%20sent%20a%20detailed%20analysis%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill%2C%20highlighting%20issues%20such%20as%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20independence%20of%20the%20oversight%20body.%20But%20the%20Bill%20continues%20to%20suffer%20from%20the%20same%20problems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fregressive-amendments-to-rti-act-ncpri-flags-concerns-over-digital-personal-data-protection-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fan%20dances%20on%20'Zinda%20Banda'%20with%20grandmother%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691137395000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102420313%2Cimgsize-36688.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Ffan-shakes-a-leg-on-shah-rukh-khans-zinda-banda-with-his-grandmother-director-atlee-reacts-see-post%2Farticleshow%2F102420313.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102420313.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EShah%20Rukh%20Khan's%20latest%20song%20'Zinda%20Banda'%20has%20become%20a%20hit%20among%20his%20fans%20across%20India.%20The%20song%20has%20been%20released%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Tamil%2C%20and%20Telugu%20languages%2C%20and%20many%20fans%20have%20shared%20videos%20of%20themselves%20dancing%20to%20it%20on%20social%20media.%20Composed%20by%20Anirudh%20Ravichander%2C%20the%20music%20video%20features%20a%20young%20Shah%20Rukh%20dancing%20with%20hundreds%20of%20women%2C%20including%20Sanya%20Malhotra%20and%20Priya%20Mani.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Ffan-shakes-a-leg-on-shah-rukh-khans-zinda-banda-with-his-grandmother-director-atlee-reacts-see-post%2Farticleshow%2F102420313.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20surname%20case%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20stays%20conviction%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691137382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F