419%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fandrea-hoyos-valves-autoerotic-1235687419%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fandrea-hoyos-valves-autoerotic-1235687419%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Violations%20Continue%20in%20J%26K%2C%20Hold%20Assembly%20Elections%20Immediately'%3A%20Report%20on%20Human%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113220%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230756_004.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Five%20years%20since%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20without%20an%20elected%20government%20and%20four%20years%20after%20the%20revocation%20of%20its%20special%20status%20under%20Article%20370%2C%20human%20rights%20violations%20have%20continued%20in%20the%20region%2C%20making%20it%20imperative%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20hold%20assembly%20elections%2C%20a%20new%20report%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Forum%20for%20Human%20Rights%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20an%20independent%20body%20of%20concerned%20citizens%2C%20released%20its%20fourth%20annual%20report%20on%20Thursday%20titled%20%E2%80%9CFive%20Years%20Without%20an%20Elected%20Administration%3A%20Human%20Rights%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20August%202022%20%E2%80%93%20July%202023%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20was%20launched%20by%20the%20Forum%20along%20with%20National%20Conference%20president%20Farooq%20Abdullah%2C%20and%20members%20of%20parliament%20Manoj%20Jha%20(RJD)%2C%20Supriya%20Sule%20(NCP)%2C%20Kanimozhi%20(DMK)%2C%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20(Congress)%2C%20Sitaram%20Yechury%20(CPI-M)%20and%20Mohammad%20Yusuf%20Tarigami%20(PAGD).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20co-chairs%20of%20the%20Forum%20include%20Gopal%20Pillai%2C%20former%20home%20secretary%2C%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20Radha%20Kumar%2C%20former%20member%2C%20Group%20of%20Interlocutors%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20report%20found%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20has%20said%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20counter%20affidavit%20filed%20last%20month%20that%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%20of%20August%209%2C%202019%2C%20had%20brought%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9Cunprecedented%20development%2C%20progress%2C%20security%20and%20stability%20to%20the%20region%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20facts%20suggest%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20found%20that%20while%20there%20has%20been%20improvement%20on%20some%20parameters%2C%20human%20rights%20violations%20continue%20on%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20number%20of%20lives%20lost%20due%20to%20armed%20attacks%20and%20counter-insurgency%20operations%20was%20lower%20than%20in%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20the%20number%20of%20police%20personnel%20who%20died%2C%20including%20Central%20Reserve%20Police%20Forces%20(CRPF)%2C%20continues%20to%20be%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C71%20CRPF%20troops%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20four%20years%20between%202019-2022%2C%20twice%20as%20many%20as%20in%20the%20previous%20four%20years%2C%202014-2018%2C%20when%2035%20died.%20By%20comparison%2C%20in%20the%20four%20years%20between%202012-2015%2C%20which%20can%20be%20categorised%20as%20an%20uneasy%20interregnum%20between%20the%20post-peace%20process%20years%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20BJP-PDP%20coalition%2C%2027%20CRPF%20troops%20were%20killed%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20also%20drawn%20attention%20to%20the%20resurgence%20of%20militancy%20in%20Jammu%20after%20decades%20of%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%202022%20delimitation%20of%20fresh%20legislative%20constituencies%2C%20adding%20Poonch%20and%20Rajouri%20to%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Anantnag%2C%20may%20have%20added%20to%20the%20alienation%20that%20these%20Muslim-majority%20areas%20face%20with%20the%20sharpening%20of%20communal%20divides%20in%20Jammu%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20improvement%20in%20gross%20violations%20of%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20movement%2C%20especially%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20media%2C%20and%20pointed%20to%20the%20arrests%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20and%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20(PSA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20Delhi%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20undertrials%20as%20a%20proportion%20of%20its%20prison%20population%20at%2091%25%2C%20against%20the%20national%20average%20of%2076%25%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region%E2%80%99s%20prisons%20can%20house%20a%20total%20of%203%2C629%20inmates%2C%20but%20they%20lodged%205%2C300%20as%20of%20June%202023%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20at%2023.1%25%20in%20March%202023%2C%20unemployment%20was%20almost%20three%20times%20the%20national%20average%20of%207.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20while%20a%20record%20year%20of%20tourism%20in%202022%20has%20boosted%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20still%20lags%20behind%20the%20national%20average%20on%20per%20capita%20income%20and%20rates%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeed%20to%20hold%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20demand%20of%20the%20report%20is%20to%20highlight%20the%20need%20for%20holding%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20well%20as%20a%20legislative%20assembly%20in%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20nine%20years%20since%20the%20last%20legislative%20election%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20union%20administration%20accepted%20the%20delimitation%20commission%E2%80%99s%20report%20a%20year%20ago%20and%20it%20is%20eight%20months%20since%20fresh%20electoral%20rolls%20were%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20preparations%20for%20an%20election%20have%20thus%20been%20completed%2C%20but%20the%20election%20commission%20has%20yet%20to%20announce%20dates%20for%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20said%20that%20the%20report%20highlights%20the%20need%20to%20hold%20elections%20because%20the%20right%20to%20vote%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRight%20to%20vote%20and%20periodic%20and%20regular%20elections%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20while%20releasing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHence%20we%20have%20focused%20on%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20other%20big%20concern%20is%20the%20resurgence%20of%20militancy%20in%20Jammu.%20Why%20has%20this%20resurgence%20happened%20after%20decades%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%20said%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20bridge%20the%20trust%20deficit%20that%20exists%20between%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20rulers%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20trust%20deficit%20between%20Delhi%20and%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20If%20this%20nation%20has%20to%20survive%20we%20have%20to%20survive%20together%2C%20we%20cannot%20survive%20by%20dividing%20each%20other%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20report%2C%20Tharoor%20said%20the%20figures%20of%20the%20killing%20of%20CRPF%20jawans%20reflects%20the%20tension%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20persistence%20of%20tension%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20part%20of%20India%20which%20is%20used%20to%20having%20elections%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20had%20polls%20in%20nine%20years.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20initiate%20action%20against%20those%20who%20violate%20human%20rights%20as%20well%20as%20intimidation%20of%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20must%20work%20in%20cooperation%20with%20local%20groups%20to%20ensure%20the%20return%20of%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666603%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20release%20in%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20Atul%20Ashok%20Howale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJha%20said%20that%20the%20question%20of%20Kashmir%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20whole%20and%20without%20any%20%E2%80%9Cifs%20and%20buts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20hold%20elections%20immediately.%20There%20is%20a%20huge%20difference%20between%20the%20idea%20of%20normalcy%20in%20Delhi%20and%20that%20in%20Kashmir.%20What%20we%20saw%20in%20Manipur%20also%20shows%20that%20the%20idea%20(of%20the%20government)%20is%20to%20use%20polarisation%20and%20majoritarian%20ethos%20to%20win%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESule%20said%20that%20the%20report%20highlights%20the%20failed%20promise%20of%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20who%20had%20promised%20to%20hold%20elections%20a%20year%20after%20revoking%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAmit%20Shah%20had%20promised%20elections%20in%20a%20year%20when%20he%20brought%20the%20bill%20in%20parliament.%20Now%20four%20years%20on%20that%20has%20not%20happened%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYechury%20said%20that%20if%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claims%20are%20to%20be%20believed%2C%20it%20is%20now%20an%20opportune%20moment%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGovernment%20claims%20peace%20has%20been%20restored%20and%20there%20are%20conditions%20for%20elections.%20If%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%20today%20the%20conditions%20are%20perfect%20to%20hold%20elections%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20militancy%20according%20to%20them%2C%20there%20is%20peace%20and%20tranquility-Then%20why%20are%20elections%20not%20being%20held%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRestoration%20of%20democratic%20participation%20of%20people%20will%20go%20a%20long%20way.%20Pressure%20must%20be%20mounted%20for%20immediate%20holding%20of%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20key%20recommendations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20need%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20report%20has%20recommended%20that%20the%20government%20should%20accept%20and%20implement%20the%20tribal%20welfare%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20that%20Ladakh%20be%20included%20in%20the%20sixth%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20executive%20authority%20of%20the%20Kargil%20and%20Leh%20hill%20councils%20should%20be%20restored%20and%20the%20prospect%20of%20statehood%20should%20be%20discussed%20with%20concerned%20stakeholders%20in%20Ladakh%20and%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20also%20recommended%20the%20release%20of%20all%20political%20prisoners%20who%20were%20taken%20into%20detention%20on%20or%20after%20August%204%2C%202019%2C%20repeal%20of%20the%20PSA%20and%20other%20preventive%20deten