droughts.%20According%20to%20Redfin%2C%20it%20was%20the%20top%20market%20for%20buyers%20looking%20to%20relocate%20in%20June.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what's%20driving%20the%20city's%20home%20price%20declines%3F%20Similar%20to%20Austin%20and%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Bokhari%20chops%20it%20up%20to%20the%20ebb%20and%20flow%20of%20supply%20and%20demand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillow-offers-ibuyer-sell-phoenix-homes-at-a-loss-2021-10%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20of%20iBuyers%20in%20Phoenix%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20when%20rates%20went%20up%2C%20those%20investors%20made%20losses%20on%20their%20properties%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20As%20demand%20falls%20and%20interest%20rates%20remain%20high%2C%20those%20investors%20are%20trying%20to%20reduce%20their%20presence%20in%20the%20market%2C%20which%20has%20helped%20to%20bring%20prices%20back%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20starter%20home%20prices%20decreased%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Austin%2C%20and%20Phoenix%2C%20Redfin%20found%20that%20the%20typical%20starter%20home%20sold%20for%20a%20record%20%24243%2C000%20in%20June.%20That's%20up%202.1%25%20from%20June%202022%20and%20up%20more%20than%2045%25%20from%20the%20same%20time%20period%20in%202019.%20For%20the%20average%20first-time%20buyer%2C%20that%20means%20an%20annual%20income%20of%20about%20%2464%2C500%20is%20needed%20to%20comfortably%20afford%20the%20purchase%20of%20a%20starter%20home%20%E2%80%94%20%247%2C200%20more%20than%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20prices%20for%20the%20most%20affordable%20homes%20continue%20to%20climb%20and%20rates%20remain%20elevated%2C%20it's%20becoming%20more%20true%20that%20you%20have%20to%20be%20wealthy%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20it's%20your%20first%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Bokhari%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarter-home-price