Magistrate%20of%20Varanasi%20and%20Varanasi%20Police%20Commissioner%2C%20ASI%20additional%20director%20general%20Alok%20Tripathi%20said%20that%20the%20government%20agency%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cresuming%20archaeological%20survey%20and%20scientific%20investigation%20from%20early%20morning%E2%80%9D%20of%20August%204%2C%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ASI%20official%20requested%20the%20Varanasi%20administration%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20access%20to%20the%20site%20as%20well%20as%20adequate%20security%20to%20the%20survey%20team%20for%20their%20work%20and%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20administration%20has%20shared%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20ASI%20letter%20with%20the%20parties%20involved%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESayid%20Yasin%2C%20joint%20secretary%20of%20the%20Anjuman%20Intejamia%20Masajid%2C%20the%20caretaker%20of%20the%20masjid%2C%20shared%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20letter%2C%20which%20was%20sent%20to%20him%20by%20the%20administration%2C%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98No%20regard%20for%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20Chief%20Justice%20(CJ)%2C%20Pritinker%20Diwaker%2C%20earlier%20on%20August%203%20dismissed%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%2C%20challenging%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20judge%E2%80%99s%20July%2021%20order%20for%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20premises%20by%20the%20ASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20restoring%20the%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20district%20judge%2C%20Varanasi%2C%20C.J.%20Diwaker%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20scientific%20survey%2Finvestigation%20proposed%20to%20be%20carried%20out%E2%80%9D%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnecessary%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20justice%20and%20shall%20benefit%20the%20plaintiffs%20and%20defendants%20alike%20and%20come%20in%20aid%20of%20the%20trial%20court%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20just%20decision.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYasin%20was%20dismayed%20by%20the%20verdict.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20filled%20with%20regret%20that%20we%20lost%20one%20Babri%20Masjid%20thinking%20that%20it%20would%20protect%20the%20others.%20But%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20end%20to%20what%20others%20we%20may%20lose.%20What%E2%80%99s%20worse%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20regard%20for%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20restored%20the%20order%20of%20the%20district%20judge%2C%20who%20had%20in%20July%20directed%20the%20ASI%20director%20to%20undertake%20scientific%20investigation%2C%20survey%20or%20excavation%20at%20the%20site%2C%20i.e.%2C%20settlement%20plot%20no.%209130%2C%20excluding%20the%20areas%20(the%20ablution%20tank)%20sealed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20court%20had%20also%20directed%20the%20ASI%20to%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20scientific%20investigation%20by%20using%20GPR%20Survey%2C%20excavation%2C%20dating%20method%2C%20and%20other%20modern%20techniques%20of%20the%20present%20structure%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20it%20had%20been%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20structure%20of%20the%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20passed%20the%20directions%20in%20the%20application%20moved%20by%20four%20Hindu%20women%20in%20a%20suit%20that%20had%20been%20filed%20last%20year%20by%20them%20seeking%20year-round%20access%20for%20worship%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20compound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20also%20said%20that%20it%20had%20%E2%80%9Cno%20reason%20to%20doubt%E2%80%9D%20the%20statements%20made%20by%20the%20ASI%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20damage%20is%20going%20to%20be%20caused%20to%20the%20property%20in%20question%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20archaeological%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearings%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20sought%20assistance%20of%20the%20ASI%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETripathi%20then%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20in%20the%20court%20saying%20that%20the%20ASI%20will%20conduct%20a%20survey%2C%20documentation%2C%20photography%2C%20detail%20description%2C%20GPR%20survey%2C%20and%20full%20studies%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20harming%20the%20existing%20structures%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ASI%20would%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20survey%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20law%20and%20prepare%20a%20list%20of%20the%20antiquities%20which%20are%20found%20in%20the%20building%20and%20carry%20out%20a%20detailed%20survey%20and%20undertake%20the%20exercise%20to%20find%20the%20age%20and%20nature%20of%20the%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETripathi%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20the%20survey%20works%20would%20be%20carried%20out%20without%20any%20damage%20to%20the%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scientific%20investigation%20would%20be%20carried%20out%20beyond%20the%20structure%20and%20in%20open%20areas%20only%3B%20no%20drilling%2C%20no%20cutting%2C%20no%20removal%20of%20brick%20or%20stones%20from%20the%20existing%20structure%20will%20be%20done%20while%20conducting%20the%20survey%20and%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20survey%20would%20be%20conducted%20by%20non-destructive%20method%20by%20using%20techniques%20such%20as%20GPR%20survey%2C%20GPS%20survey%2C%20the%20other%20scientific%20methods%20and%20other%20modern%20techniques.%20In%20case%20any%20further%20investigation%20or%20excavation%20is%20required%2C%20the%20ASI%20would%20seek%20permission%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApprehensions%20that%20the%20building%20may%20get%20damaged%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20jubilant%20Vishnu%20Shankar%20Jain%2C%20one%20of%20the%20lawyers%20representing%20the%20Hindu%20petitioners%2C%20while%20talking%20to%20the%20reporters%20in%20Prayagraj%2C%20said%20that%20the%20survey%20should%20start%20soon.%20%E2%80%9CWhatever%20there%20is%2C%20truth%20or%20lies%2C%20should%20come%20out%20before%20the%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarman%20S.%20Naqvi%2C%20senior%20lawyer%20appearing%20for%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20committee%2C%20however%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20he%20was%20not%20convinced%20by%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20assurance%20on%20ensuring%20that%20the%20structure%20would%20not%20be%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20beginning%2C%20we%20have%20had%20apprehensions%20that%20the%20building%20may%20get%20damaged%20because%20it%20is%20an%20old%20structure.%20We%20claim%20it%20is%20600%20years%20old.%20The%20other%20side%20claims%20that%20it%20is%20even%20older%20%E2%80%93%201%2C000%20years.%20The%20building%20is%20not%20made%20from%20modern%20material%20or%20with%20modern%20technology.%20If%20a%20loose%20brick%20falls%20from%20somewhere%2C%20who%20will%20be%20responsible%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaqvi%20further%20said%20that%20there%20was%20no%20similar%20precedent%20of%20a%20survey%20on%20an%20old%20structure%20to%20rely%20on%20or%20independent%20scientific%20advice%20on%20what%20methods%20would%20be%20or%20have%20been%20used%20in%20similar%20cases.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20guarantee%20is%20there%20that%20it%20will%20not%20be%20damaged%2C%E2%80%9D%20asked%20Naqvi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Diwaker%20found%20no%20substance%20in%20the%20Masjid%20committee%E2%80%99s%20argument%20that%20during%20the%20scientific%20investigation%2C%20if%20any%20excavation%20was%20carried%20out%2C%20it%20would%20damage%20the%20structure.%20%C2%A0The%20court%20said%20that%20the%20ASI%20affidavit%20had%20mentioned%20that%20they%20would%20not%20carry%20out%20any%20excavation.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691084104000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F18123926%2F2022_5img17_May_2022_PTI05_17_2022_000125B-min.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fasi-to-st