3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20also%20saw%20MPs%2C%20including%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20(Congress)%2C%20Supriya%20Sule%20(Nationalist%20Congress%20Party)%2C%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20(AIMIM)%2C%20Rajiv%20Ranjan%20Singh%20(Janata%20Dal%20(United))%2C%20Dayanidhi%20Maran%20(Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam)%2C%20Kalyan%20Banerjee%20(Trinamool%20Congress)%2C%20among%20others%20speaking%20against%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20called%20it%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20federal%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20assault%20on%20the%20mandate%20to%20the%20elected%20government%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOwaisi%20said%20that%20while%20he%20was%20against%20the%20Bill%2C%20he%20also%20lashed%20out%20at%20the%20AAP%20for%20supporting%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20goes%20around%20comes%20around.%20You%20(AAP)%20cannot%20play%20victim%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20want%20to%20pose%20a%20question%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20tabled%20a%20Bill%20in%20this%20house%20for%20complete%20statehood.%20What%20is%20your%20policy%3F%20Why%20is%20the%20government%20demeaning%20the%20dignity%20of%20this%20house.%20We%20want%20to%20know%20your%20position%20on%20that.%20Take%20your%20political%20fights%20outside%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETharoor%20highlighted%20that%20the%20Bill%20was%20%E2%80%98undemocratic%E2%80%99%20and%20was%20being%20brought%20in%20while%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20was%20pending%20which%20goes%20against%20democratic%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDMK%20MP%20Maran%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20comes%20as%20the%20BJP%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20win%20elections%20in%20Delhi%20in%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20formula%20followed%20by%20the%20home%20minister%20is%20simple.%20Wherever%20BJP%20cannot%20win%2C%20we%20will%20send%20the%20ED%2C%20CBI.%20Till%20then%20they%20are%20culprits%20and%20thieves.%20We%20saw%20what%20happened%20in%20Maharashtra%20where%20you%20called%20the%20NCP%20National%20Corrupt%20Party%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accused%20the%20BJP%20of%20double%20speak%20on%20corruption%2C%20citing%20both%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20the%20previous%20Karnataka%20government%20as%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20moment%20they%20come%20to%20you%2C%20they%20are%20clean%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%20finds%20support%20in%20BJD%20and%20YSRCP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20government%20found%20favour%20from%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20the%20YSR%20Congress%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20criticism%20about%20supporting%20the%20BJP%2C%20when%20the%20Bill%20was%20introduced%2C%20BJD%20MP%20Pinaki%20Misra%20said%20that%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20support%20is%20only%20to%20the%20Bill%20and%20not%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20excitement%20has%20been%20created%20by%20the%20BJD%20supporting%20the%20Bill.%20The%20reason%20is%20not%20that%20we%20support%20the%20BJP.%20You%20will%20find%20a%20rigorous%20opposition%20against%20the%20BJP%20in%20Odisha%20on%20the%20ground%20level.%20The%20Congress%20has%20been%20wiped%20out%20in%20Odisha.%20We%20are%20equidistant%20from%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress.%20The%20reason%20we%20support%20this%20is%20because%20we%20have%20studied%20the%20constitutional%20provisions%20of%20the%20power%20of%20parliament%20to%20enact%20this%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPV%20Mithun%20Reddy%20of%20the%20YSRCP%2C%20while%20supporting%20the%20Bill%2C%20however%2C%20urged%20the%20government%20to%20not%20bring%20the%20legislation%20to%20other%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20unique%20Bill%20and%20I%20hope%20that%20this%20Bill%20is%20not%20replicated%20for%20other%20states%20and%20with%20this%20we%20support%20this%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20also%20saw%20BJP%20MPs%2C%20including%20Meenakshi%20Lekhi%2C%20Parvesh%20Singh%20Sahib%2C%20Ramesh%20Bhiduri%2C%20among%20others%2C%20supporting%20the%20Bill%20and%20accusing%20the%20AAP%20of%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh%20drama%20as%20Bill%20is%20passed%20by%20voice%20vote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20ended%20with%20high%20drama%20as%20the%20opposition%20walked%20out%20just%20before%20the%20division%20of%20votes%20was%20called%20by%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20and%20AAP%20MP%20Sushil%20Kumar%20Rinku%20was%20suspended%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20monsoon%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20responding%20to%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20closing%20statement%2C%20Chowdhury%20said%20that%20the%20home%20minister%20had%20used%20the%20opportunity%20of%20the%20debate%20to%20deliver%20an%20election%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShah%20has%20shown%20that%20he%20is%20in%20election%20mode.%20Today%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20saying%20that%20there%20is%20no%20law%20and%20order%20in%20Manipur.%20We%20wanted%20a%20discussion%20on%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChowdhury%20was%20drowned%20out%20by%20loud%20sloganeering.%20Subsequently%2C%20he%20emerged%20from%20the%20House%20and%20told%20ANI%20that%20he%20was%20not%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20respond%20to%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20election%20speech%20and%20the%20opposition%20had%20no%20option%20but%20to%20walk%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20least%20today%2C%20he%20(Shah)%20should%20be%20ashamed%20of%20the%20Manipur%20incident.%20If%20we%20do%20not%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20present%20our%20views%20in%20the%20House%20and%20the%20home%20minister%20starts%20with%20his%20election%20speech%20but%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20to%20respond%2C%20what%20choice%20do%20we%20have..so%20we%20walked%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1687109385368276994%5C