Ashirwad%20Mahaprashasta%2FThe%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20demolished%20shanties%20bore%20a%20desolate%20look.%20Surrounded%20by%20glitzy%20high%20rises%2C%20these%20temporary%20houses%20were%20made%20of%20tin%20and%20asbestos%20sheets.%20%E2%80%9CLook%20at%20the%20condition%20in%20which%20they%20lived.%20There%20is%20no%20drinking%20water%3B%20no%20bathrooms%2C%20no%20proper%20lights.%20They%20had%20absolutely%20nothing.%20Yet%2C%20they%20became%20an%20eyesore%20for%20the%20mob%20just%20because%20they%20were%20Muslims%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yadav.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20vegetable-seller%20Pinku%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20people%20have%20been%20living%20here%20for%20many%20years.%20They%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20Nuh%20violence.%20Yet%2C%20they%20became%20the%20targets.%20The%20mob%20was%20out%20here%20for%20revenge.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Yadav%20and%20Pinku%20added%20that%20the%20mob%20looted%20houses%20and%20shops%20before%20setting%20them%20on%20fire.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20see%20that%20the%20cash%20counter%20is%20empty%20in%20the%20dhaba%20that%20got%20burnt.%20They%20left%20nothing%2C%20stole%20even%20chairs%20and%20tables%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yadav%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuslim%20immigrants%20forced%20to%20flee%20overnight%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20these%20Muslim%20immigrants%20stayed%20with%20their%20families%2C%20and%20were%20forced%20to%20flee%20overnight.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20scared%2C%20so%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20a%20chance.%20Once%20I%20heard%20that%20my%20shop%20had%20been%20demolished%2C%20I%20came%20to%20Sambhal%20with%20my%20family%2C%E2%80%9D%20Md.%20Shahid%2C%20manager%20of%20Mahak%20Cotton%20Store%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShahid%20said%20that%20he%20never%20had%20an%20inkling%20that%20the%20Nuh%20violence%20would%20affect%20them%20too.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20riots%20happened%20in%20Nuh%20which%20is%2050%20kilometres%20away%20from%20Badshahpur.%20What%20did%20we%20do%20to%20deserve%20this%20kind%20of%20treatment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fharyana-violence-mewat-hate-and-provocative-videos%5C%22%3EHaryana%20Violence%3A%20How%20Provocative%20Videos%20and%20a%20Background%20of%20Hate%20Preceded%20the%20Nuh%20Riots%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20managing%20the%20store%20since%202009.%20I%20had%20friendly%20relations%20with%20everyone.%20Even%20Parwez%2C%20who%20owned%20the%20juice%20shop%20across%20the%20street%2C%20was%20friendly%20with%20everyone%20in%20the%20neighbourhood.%20Yet%2C%20I%20hear%20that%20some%20people%20of%20Badshahpur%20directed%20the%20mob%20towards%20our%20shops.%20I%20also%20heard%20that%20some%20of%20those%20who%20stole%20things%20from%20my%20shops%20were%20people%20whom%20I%20knew%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shahid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBadshahpur%20remained%20tense%20amidst%20police%20presence%20throughout%20the%20last%20two%20days.%20The%20old%20mosque%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20village%20was%20locked%20with%20police%20guarding%20its%20premises.%20A%20few%20Muslims%20who%20were%20residents%20of%20the%20village%20appear%20to%20have%20fled.%20Villagers%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20some%20of%20them%20were%20still%20there%20but%20had%20not%20left%20their%20houses%20at%20all%2C%20and%20had%20kept%20them%20locked.%20A%20temple%20stood%20right%20adjacent%20to%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVillage%20elders%20claimed%20that%20no%20one%20from%20Badshahpur%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20violence%2C%20and%20that%20everyone%20in%20the%20mob%20was%20an%20outsider.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20never%20had%20any%20communal%20disturbance%20here.%20The%20Muslim%20homes%20you%20see%E2%80%A6%5Bpeople%5D%20have%20been%20living%20here%20since%20the%20last%20200%20years.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20we%20watched%20an%20incident%20like%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20one%20among%20the%20elders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mob%2C%20however%2C%20didn%E2%80%99t%20merely%20target%20the%20shanties%20and%20shops%20around%20Badshahpur.%20It%20entered%20the%20village%20to%20target%20two%20meat%20shops%20owned%20by%20two%20old%20residents%20of%20the%20village.%20The%20meat%20shops%20were%20destroyed%20and%20looted%2C%20following%20which%20even%20the%20old%20Muslim%20residents%20left%20the%20village.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F03185851%2FIMG_3952.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F03185851%2FIMG_3952.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F03185851%2FIMG_3952-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F03185851%2FIMG_3952-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666533%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMeat%20shop%20owned%20by%20a%20village%20resident.%20Photo%3A%20Ajoy%20Ashirwad%20Mahaprashasta%2FThe%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20village%20youth%2C%20however%2C%20justified%20the%20violence.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Muslims%20beat%20the%20Hindus%20first%20in%20Nuh.%20What%20happened%20here%20was%20a%20reaction%20to%20the%20Nuh%20violence%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Arun%2C%20even%20as%20some%20elders%20around%20him%20tried%20to%20stop%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20two%2015-year-old%20boys%20of%20Badshahpur%20seemed%20excited%20that%20Muslim%20immigrants%20had%20fled.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20shops%20which%20were%20attacked%20were%20owned%20by%20Mullahs.%20They%20did%20not%20belong%20here.%20Good%20that%20they%20left%2C%20or%20else%20we%20would%20have%20made%20them%20run%20for%20their%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20one%20of%20them%20proudly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20deepened%20communal%20animosity%20against%20Muslims%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReligious%20polarisation%20ran%20deep%2C%20despite%20a%20consensus%20among%20Hindus%20that%20the%20mob%20violence%20and%20subsequent%20looting%20of%20Muslim%20establishments%20may%20have%20tarnished%20the%20perception%20of%20the%20village.%20Rumours%20of%20various%20kinds%20ran%20the%20show%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20violence.%20Almost%20everyone%20in%20Badshahpur%20spoke%20about%20how%20on%20Wednesday%20morning%20a%20Muslim%20man%20allegedly%20killed%20a%20Hindu%20shopkeeper%20in%20Maruti%20Kunj%2C%20a%20locality%20merely%20a%20kilometre%20away%20from%20the%20village.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20upon%20enquiry%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20found%20that%20no%20such%20killing%20had%20taken%20place.%20But%20Badshahpur%20residents%20believed%20the%20rumour%20to%20be%20true%2C%20and%20that%20has%20only%20deepened%20their%20communal%20animosity%20against%20Muslims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%20two%20kilometres%20away%2C%20a%20slum%20in%20Sector%2070%2C%20where%20Muslim%20immigrants%20from%20West%20Bengal%20lived%2C%20was%20similarly%20destroyed%20and%20looted%20by%20the%20Hindutva%20mob.%20Most%20of%20them%20fled%20overnight.%20Those%20who%20remain%2C%20fear%20for%20their%20safety%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20assurance%20from%20government%20agencies.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20onlookers%20had%20a%20field%20day%20in%20Badshahpur%20with%20television%20OBs%2C%20journalists%2C%20civil%20society%20activists%20visiting%20the%20village.%20Many%20of%20them%20were%20amused%20with%20so%20much%20attention.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20feels%20like%20an%20action%20film%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20eight-year-old%20kid%20from%20Badshahpur%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20swanky%20offices%2C%20luxurious%20high%20rises%2C%20and%20smooth%20flyovers%20have%20come%20to%20dwarf%20villages%20like%20Badshahpur%20%E2%80%93%20making%20the%20residents%20feel%20trapped%20in%20their%20settlements%20amidst%20the%20development%20fancies%20of%20the%20millennium%20city.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20its%20way%20to%20becoming%20a%20business%20destination%2C%20villages%20like%20Badshahpur%20in%20the%20greater%20Gurugram%20area%20have%20become%20a%20home%20to%20numerous%20working%20class%20immigrants%20who%20worked%20behind%20the%20veil%20to%20keep%20the%20city%20running.%20They%20lived%20in%20their%20temporary%20shanties%20to%20earn%20a%20livelihood%2C%20but%20could%20not%20afford%20to%20complain%20about%20their%20daily%20struggles.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20governments%2C%20too%2C%20did%20not%20spare%20a%20look%20at%20their%20abysmal%20living%20conditions.%20Their%20labour%20is%20cheap%20and%20essential%20for%20the%20development%20goals%20of%20the%20city.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20shanties%20of%20Gurugram%20have%20suddenly%20shot%20to%20limelight%2C%20even%20as%20hundreds%20of%20Muslim%20workers%20flee%20the%20millennium%20city.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691079374000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F03191741%2Fed5381de-ca05-4069-ace5-f6ea6089017b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fi-was-scared-didnt-take-a-