nds%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Be%20Sent%20to%20Parliamentary%20Committee%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F25143729%2Fdata-protection-1200x600.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKolkata%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20on%20Thursday%20(August%203)%20tabled%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20(DPDP)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20as%20opposition%20members%20demanded%20that%20the%20Bill%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20that%20the%20legislation%20is%20being%20brought%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprovide%20for%20the%20processing%20of%20digital%20personal%20data%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20recognises%20both%20the%20right%20of%20individuals%20to%20protect%20their%20personal%20data%20and%20the%20need%20to%20process%20such%20personal%20data%20for%20lawful%20purposes%20and%20for%20matters%20connected%20therewith%20or%20incidental%20thereto.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinister%20for%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%20tabled%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20through%20a%20voice%20vote%20after%20concerns%20were%20raised%20by%20opposition%20members%20about%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20in%20the%20legislation%2C%20as%20well%20as%20dangers%20it%20poses%20to%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpersonal-data-protection-bill-will-severely-restrict-scope-of-rti-act-activists-write-to-mps%5C%22%3EPersonal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Will%20%E2%80%98Severely%20Restrict%20Scope%20of%20RTI%20Act%E2%80%99%3A%20Activists%20Write%20to%20MPs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposing%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20All%20India%20Majlis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%20(AIMIM)%20MP%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20Article%2019%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%2C%20which%20guarantees%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20access%20people%E2%80%99s%20private%20data%20and%20is%20likely%20to%20create%20a%20surveillance%20state.%20The%20Bill%20is%20also%20anti-women%2C%20as%20only%20one%20in%20three%20women%20in%20India%20use%20the%20internet%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20and%20asked%20for%20a%20division%20of%20votes%20on%20whether%20the%20Bill%20should%20be%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20leader%20of%20the%20house%20and%20Congress%20MP%2C%20Gaurav%20Gogoi%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20should%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20a%20standing%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSend%20the%20Bill%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%20as%20it%20infringes%20upon%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20privacy%20as%20per%20%5Bthe%5D%20%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3Cins%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20a%20nine-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20unanimously%20delivered%20its%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-chandrachud-judgment-right-to-privacy%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJustice%20K.S.%20Puttaswamy%20(Retd.)%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20held%20that%20privacy%20is%20a%20constitutionally%20protected%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20not%20only%20emerges%20from%20the%20guarantee%20of%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%20in%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20but%20also%20arises%20in%20varying%20contexts%20from%20the%20other%20facets%20of%20freedom%20and%20dignity%20recognised%20and%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20contained%20in%20Part%20III%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEchoing%20the%20demand%20to%20send%20the%20Bill%20back%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%2C%20Trinamool%20Congress%20MP%20Saugata%20Roy%20said%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccumbersome%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20cumbersome%20Bill%20and%20very%20different%20from%20the%20original%20Bill%20which%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20standing%20committee.%20The%20chairman%20of%20the%20standing%20committee%20has%20changed%20the%20Bill%20altogether.%20I%20want%20this%20Bill%20to%20be%20again%20sent%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20MPs%20who%20are%20members%20of%20the%20department-related%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Communications%20and%20Information%20Technology%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fopposition-activists-raise-alarm-as-modi-govt-gets-ready-to-pass-data-protection-bill%5C%22%3Eearlier%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20committee%20had%20adopted%20a%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Citizen%E2%80%99s%20data%20security%20and%20privacy%E2%80%99%20on%20July%2026.%20The%20report%20examines%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20and%20contains%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20on%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20opposition%20members%20in%20the%20committee%20said%20they%20do%20not%20approve%20of%20the%20report%2C%20mainly%20because%2C%20according%20to%20them%2C%20the%20report%20was%20prepared%20by%20the%20committee%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjohn-brittas-data-protection-bill-panel-opposition-parliament%5C%22%3Ebypassing%20parliamentary%20procedure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20requires%20a%20Bill%20to%20be%20first%20introduced%20in%20either%20a%20House%20of%20the%20parliament%2C%20before%20it%20can%20be%20referred%20to%20a%20standing%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20members%20also%20alleged%20that%20they%20have%20not%20seen%20the%20final%20Bill%20and%20had%20very%20little%20time%20with%20the%20report%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20Manish%20Tewari%2C%20while%20demanding%20that%20the%20Bill%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee%2C%20said%20that%20the%20legislation%20cannot%20be%20introduced%20as%20a%20finance%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20Bill%2C%20which%20was%20considered%20by%20the%20JPC%20%5Bjoint%20parliamentary%20committee%5D%2C%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20House%2C%20and%20then%20withdrawn%20cannot%20be%20introduced%20as%20a%20finance%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.a%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Thursday%20morning%2C%20Tewari%20had%20said%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdata-protection-bill-controversy-widens-congress-mp-jpc-member-says-classified-as-money-bill%5C%22%3E%20planning%20to%20introduce%20the%20Bill%20as%20a%20finance%20Bill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20it%20to%20not%20seek%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20Bill%20which%20requires%20serious%20reconsideration%20by%20a%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee%20for%20the%20simple%20reason%20that%20it%20is%20in%20complete%20contradiction%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20upheld%20by%20the%20%5BSupreme%20Court%5D%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20Bill%20cleaves%20the%20digital%20universe%20into%20two%20parts%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Bill%20will%20apply%20with%20full%20force%20on%20all%20non-governmental%20organisations%2C%20and%20the%20entire%20government%20universe%20is%20going%20to%20be%20exempt%20from%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdata-protection-bull-proliferation-digital-india%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Won%E2%80%99t%20Stop%20Data%20Proliferation%20in%20Digital%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Different%20versions%20of%20the%20Bill%20do%20not%20match%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Bill%20was%20tabled%20on%20Thursday%20after%20the%20cabinet%20gave%20its%20approval%20on%20July%205%2C%20the%20legislation%20has%20been%20in%20the%20works%20for%20several%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20first%20constituted%20a%20Committee%20of%20Experts%20on%20Data%20Protection%20chaired%20by%20Justice%20B.N.%20Srikrishna%20to%20examine%20issues%20relating%20to%20data%20protection%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202019%2C%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20December%202019%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20committee%20report%2C%20which%20was%20submitted%20in%20July%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20was%20then%20referred%20to%20a%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%2C%20which%20submitted%20its%20report%20in%20December%202021.%20The%20following%20August%2C%20the%20Bill%20was%20withdrawn%20from%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202022%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20released%20the%20Draft%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20for%20public%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20said%20that%20since%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20modified%20several%20times%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20standing%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20disappointment%20that%20to%20the%20best%20of%20my%20knowledge%20the%20committee%20has%20not%20been%20asked%20to%20study%20this%20Bill%2C%20which%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20modified%20and%20is%20being%20brought%20in%20its%20third%20reiteration.%20I%20urge%20the%20Bill%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20standing%20comm%20as%20a%20new%20Bill%20because%20the%20three%20different%20versions%20do%20not%20match%20and%20they%20have%20been%20brought%20without%20consulting%20the%20committee%20whose%20mandate%20it%20is%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERevolutionary%20Socialist%20Party%3C%2Fspan%3E%20MP%20N.K.%20Premachandran%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20does%20not%20take%20into%20account%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20standing%20committee%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20standing%20committee%20submitted%20a%20report%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%20(August%201).%20There%20are%20so%20many%20recommendations.%20Without%20looking%20at%20the%20recommendations%2C%20they%20have%20come%20up%20with%20a%20new%20Bill%20which%20is%20not%20fair%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Penalty%20but%20no%20compensation%20for%20data%20theft%20victims%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20and%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20MP%20Supriya%20Sule%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20compensation%20for%20victims%20of%20data%20theft%20in%20the%20Bill%20and%20the%20amendments%20made%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Bill%20allows%20excessive%20centralisation%20of%20all%20data%2C%20and%20it%20is%20a%20complete%20insult%20to%20the%20federal%20structure%2C%20and%20it%20dilutes%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fopposition-activists-raise-alarm-as-modi-govt-gets-ready-to-pass-data-protection-bill%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20earlier%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20concerns%20raised%20by%20activists%20who%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%20by%20severely%20restricting%20its%20scope.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESule%20added%20that%20while%20there%20is%20a%20penalty%20for%20data%20theft%2C%20the%20victim%20is%20not%20protected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20penalty%20but%20no%20compensation.%20What%20about%20a%20victim%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChowdhury%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20will%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20corruption%20by%20amending%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThrough%20this%20Bill%2C%20the%20government%20will%20trample%20upon%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20vehemently%20opposing%20this%20sinister%20motive%20by%20the%20government%20as%20by%20amending%20the%20RTI%2C%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20introduce%20a%20new%20era%20of%20corruption%20where%20personal%20data%20like%20assets%20and%20liabilities%2C%20educational%20qualifications%20of%20corrupt%20government%20officials%20cannot%20be%20asked%20under%20RTI%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Bill%20does%20not%20provide%20compensation%20to%20individuals%20whose%20personal%20data%20has%20been%20compromised%20or%20%5Bthose%20who%5D%20suffered%20losses%20due%20to%20personal%20data%20theft%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20present%20Bill%20does%20not%20restrict%20the%20government%20from%20storing%20and%20using%20personal%20data.%20l%20suggest%20the%20government%20put%20out%20the%20Bill%20for%20further%20deliberation%20and%20wide%20discussion%20among%20all%20sections%20of%20the%20population%2C%20send%20it%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%20or%20a%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee%20or%20any%20other%20forum%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20introducing%20the%20Bill%2C%20Vaishnaw%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20contrary%20to%20concerns%20about%20the%20government%20bringing%20the%20legislation%20as%20a%20finance%20Bill%2C%20the%20legislation%20is%20an%20ordinary%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C(Opposition)%20members%20have%20not%20raised%20any%20questions%20on%20whether%20there%20is%20legislative%20competence%20to%20bring%20this%20Bill.%20Instead%20they%20have%20asked%20whether%20this%20is%20a%20general%20Bill%20or%20a%20finance%20Bill%20or%20a%20money%20Bill.%20I%20want%20to%20clarify%20that%20this%20is%20a%20general%20Bill%20and%20not%20a%20money%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20%5Bthe%5D%20points%20raised%20by%20%5Bthe%5D%20members%20on%20%3Cem%3EPuttaswamy%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20compensation%2C%20or%20any%20other%20objections%2C%20we%20are%20ready%20for%20a%20detailed%20debate%20on%20each%20issue%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691077042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F25143729%2Fdata-protection-1200x600.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdata-protection-bill-opposition-parliamentary-committee%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Opposition%20members%20said%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20modified%20several%20times%20%E2%80%93%20violates%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20endangers%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20studied%20by%20a%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdata-protection-bill-opposition-parliamentary-committee%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20officials%E2%80%99%20call%20to%20save%20Xi%20Jinping%E2%80%99s%20projects%20angers%20flood%20victims%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691073734000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102398383%2Cimgsize-369244.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-officials-call-to-save-xi-jinpings-projects-angers-flood-victims%2Farticleshow%2F102398299.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102398299.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EResidents%20affect